# YouTube API Setup Guide - Complete Step-by-Step

This guide will help you connect your YouTube channel to your church website so sermons automatically appear.

---

## Part 1: Get Your YouTube Channel ID

### What is a Channel ID?
A Channel ID is a unique code that identifies your YouTube channel. It looks like this: `UCLLCOdaPPPSyNe0eT4gusCw`

### Step-by-Step Instructions:

#### Step 1: Open YouTube
1. Open your web browser (Chrome, Firefox, Safari, etc.)
2. Type in the address bar: `www.youtube.com`
3. Press Enter

#### Step 2: Sign In
1. Look at the top-right corner of the page
2. Click the **"Sign in"** button
3. Enter your Google account email and password
4. Make sure you sign in with the account that owns your church's YouTube channel

#### Step 3: Go to Your Channel
1. After signing in, look at the top-right corner again
2. You'll see your profile picture or account icon
3. Click on it
4. A menu will drop down
5. Click on **"Your channel"** (it's usually the second option)

#### Step 4: Find Your Channel ID

**Method 1: Check the URL**
1. Once you're on your channel page, look at the top of your browser
2. You'll see a long web address (URL) in the address bar
3. The URL will look like one of these:
   - `https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCLLCOdaPPPSyNe0eT4gusCw`
   - `https://www.youtube.com/@YourChurchName`

**If you see the FIRST format** (with `/channel/`):
- Everything after `/channel/` is your Channel ID
- Example: If URL is `https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCLLCOdaPPPSyNe0eT4gusCw`
- Your Channel ID is: `UCLLCOdaPPPSyNe0eT4gusCw`
- ✅ Copy this and save it in a text file or notepad

**If you see the SECOND format** (with `/@`):
1. Look for a button that says **"Customize channel"** on your channel page
2. Click on it
3. Now look at the URL again - it should change to show the `/channel/` format
4. Copy the Channel ID as described above

**Alternative Method:**
1. Click on any video on your channel
2. Under the video, click on your channel name
3. This will take you to your channel page with the `/channel/` URL format
4. Copy the Channel ID from the URL

#### Step 5: Save Your Channel ID
1. Open Notepad (Windows) or TextEdit (Mac)
2. Type: `Channel ID: ` and paste your Channel ID
3. Save this file as `YouTube_Info.txt` on your desktop
4. Keep this file - you'll need it later!

---

## Part 2: Get Your YouTube API Key

### What is an API Key?
An API key is like a password that allows your website to access YouTube's data. It looks like this: `AIzaSyA5rZwWSNRSgA8uiPlIkCy6vVMDQMiMQlM`

### Step-by-Step Instructions:

#### Step 1: Go to Google Cloud Console
1. Open a new tab in your browser
2. Type in the address bar: `console.cloud.google.com`
3. Press Enter
4. You'll be taken to Google Cloud Console
5. Sign in with the SAME Google account you use for YouTube

#### Step 2: Create a New Project
1. Look at the very top of the page
2. You'll see a blue bar with "Google Cloud" logo
3. Next to the logo, you'll see a dropdown that might say "Select a project" or show a project name
4. Click on this dropdown
5. A popup window will appear showing your projects (might be empty if this is your first time)
6. Look for a button that says **"NEW PROJECT"** in the top-right of the popup
7. Click **"NEW PROJECT"**

#### Step 3: Name Your Project
1. You'll see a form with a field labeled "Project name"
2. Type: `Church Sermons Website` (or any name you like)
3. Leave the "Location" field as is (usually says "No organization")
4. Click the blue **"CREATE"** button at the bottom
5. Wait 10-20 seconds while Google creates your project
6. You'll see a notification when it's done

#### Step 4: Select Your Project
1. Click on the project dropdown again (at the top)
2. You should now see your new project "Church Sermons Website"
3. Click on it to select it
4. The top bar should now show your project name

#### Step 5: Enable YouTube Data API
1. Look at the left side of the screen - you'll see a menu (sidebar)
2. If you don't see the menu, click the "☰" (three horizontal lines) icon at the top-left
3. In the menu, find and click **"APIs & Services"**
4. A submenu will appear
5. Click on **"Library"**
6. You'll see a page with many API options

#### Step 6: Search for YouTube API
1. At the top of the page, you'll see a search box that says "Search for APIs & Services"
2. Click in the search box
3. Type: `YouTube Data API v3`
4. Press Enter or click the search icon
5. You'll see search results appear

#### Step 7: Enable the API
1. Look for **"YouTube Data API v3"** in the results (it should be the first one)
2. It will have a YouTube logo icon
3. Click on it
4. You'll be taken to a page with information about the API
5. Look for a blue button that says **"ENABLE"**
6. Click **"ENABLE"**
7. Wait a few seconds while it enables
8. The page will change to show API details

#### Step 8: Create API Credentials
1. Look at the left sidebar again
2. Click on **"Credentials"** (it's under "APIs & Services")
3. You'll see a page that might be empty or show existing credentials
4. At the top of the page, look for a button that says **"+ CREATE CREDENTIALS"**
5. Click on it
6. A dropdown menu will appear with options
7. Click on **"API key"** (it's usually the first option)

#### Step 9: Copy Your API Key
1. A popup window will appear with your new API key
2. The popup will say "API key created"
3. You'll see a long string of letters and numbers - this is your API key
4. It looks like: `AIzaSyA5rZwWSNRSgA8uiPlIkCy6vVMDQMiMQlM`
5. Click the **"COPY"** button next to the key (or select it and press Ctrl+C / Cmd+C)
6. **IMPORTANT:** Don't close this popup yet!

#### Step 10: Save Your API Key
1. Open your `YouTube_Info.txt` file (the one you created earlier)
2. On a new line, type: `API Key: ` and paste your API key
3. Save the file
4. Your file should now look like this:
```
Channel ID: UCLLCOdaPPPSyNe0eT4gusCw
API Key: AIzaSyA5rZwWSNRSgA8uiPlIkCy6vVMDQMiMQlM
```




#### Step 12: You're Done with Google Cloud!
You can now close the Google Cloud Console tab. Keep your `YouTube_Info.txt` file safe!

